.TH emu-stack @MANSECTION@ @DATE@ "version @EMU_VERSION@" "Emu Manual"
.SH NAME
emu\-stack \- manage set of emu stacks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B emu stack
[<options>]
.sp
.B emu stack
[<options>] add <stack> <path>
.sp
.B emu stack
[<options>] rm <stack>
.SH DESCRIPTION
With no arguments, show a list of existing stacks.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
add <stack> <path>
Initialises an empty stack named <stack> in the directory <path>. This
means creating a .emu directory at <path> with subdirectories for
trees and nodes. Each stack <stack> must be unique.
.TP
rm <stack>
Removes stack <stack> from the source refs. This does not affect the
stack structure and is non\-destructive.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-S <dir> \-\-source-dir <dir>
Specify the directory to use as an emu source. Defaults to `.'.
.TP
\-v \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity.
.TP
\-\-version
Show version information and quit.
.TP
\-h \-\-help
Show this help and quit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List information about stacks:
emu stack --verbose
.TP
Add a new stack `origin' at `~/backup':
emu stack add origin ~/backup
.TP
Remove stack `origin':
emu stack rm origin
.SH EMU
Part of the
.B emu
(1)
suite
